WEBVTT

00:05:57.093 --> 00:06:00.300
(Laughter)

00:06:00.324 --> 00:06:02.895
So that's the importance
of having someone there

00:06:02.919 --> 00:06:05.696
who was trained to teach you
and tell you what you do

00:06:05.720 --> 00:06:07.410
in situations like that.

00:06:08.030 --> 00:06:10.656
So, when I created
the "I'm G.R.A.C.E.D" training,

00:06:10.680 --> 00:06:13.674
I created it with that experience
that I had in mind,

00:06:13.698 --> 00:06:16.214
but also that conviction
that I had in mind.

00:06:16.238 --> 00:06:18.491
Because I wanted
the instructional design of it

00:06:18.515 --> 00:06:21.293
to be a safe space
for open dialogue for people.

00:06:21.317 --> 00:06:23.212
I wanted to talk about biases,

00:06:23.236 --> 00:06:25.633
the unconscious ones
and the conscious ones,

00:06:25.657 --> 00:06:26.823
and what we do.

00:06:26.847 --> 00:06:30.791
Because now I know
that when you engage people in the why,